1. ğŸŒ™ Dark Mode Version

Hereâ€™s how to add a simple dark mode toggle to your mobile UI.

âœ¨ Add this to your <style>:

body.dark {
  background: #121212;
}
body.dark .app {
  background: #1e1e1e;
  color: white;
}
body.dark input,
body.dark button {
  background: #333;
  color: white;
  border: 1px solid #555;
}
body.dark .nav {
  background: #222;
  border-color: #444;
}

âœ¨ Add a toggle button in your .nav section:

<button onclick="toggleDarkMode()">ğŸŒ™</button>

âœ¨ Add this to your <script>:

function toggleDarkMode() {
  document.body.classList.toggle('dark');
}

Now your mobile UI supports light/dark mode toggle like modern apps! ğŸ‰

